Dear all.=20

Applications are invited for a two-year postdoc position in mathematical =
physics and neighbouring fields. The position will be at the mathematics =
department of the university of Vienna, and also associated with the =
Erwin Schr=F6dinger Institute for Mathematical Physics, in the group of =
Nils Carqueville.=20

The group's interests include topological quantum field theory, higher =
categories, homological link invariants, 2d/4d correspondences, =
topological string theory, and categorical quantum mechanics. Both =
mathematicians and theoretical physicists with such or similar expertise =
and interests are highly encouraged to apply.=20

The position (to start in autumn of 2015) comes without any teaching =
duties, but with a comprehensive individual budget for attending =
workshops, as well as individual visits to and from other scientists.=20

To apply, please send your CV and research statement to Nils Carqueville =
(nils.carqueville@univie.ac.at), and arrange for at least two letters of =
recommendation to be sent to the same address. The application deadline =
is December 20.=20




